public class Carpenter<T,​U>

Class Carpenter implements the BiPredicate interface, so it has to provide implmentation for Test method of the BiPredicate interface. When we create a Carpenterby Carpenter<Double,String>astroDouble=new Astronaut<Double,String>() we are setting type T to be a Double and type U to be a String, which means the Consumer BiPredicate interface will also have the types T to be a Double and type U to be a String
